{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012sanMG6S6XzwcsPjnnYnHk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the coinflip domain model:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Domain Model — Complete Overview\n\n### 1. **UIMatch Type** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts`)\n\nThe `UIMatch` interface represents a match as viewed in the frontend:\n\n```typescript\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string;                    // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier;                    // iron | bronze | silver | gold | platinum | diamond\n  entryAmount: number;           // in SOL (not lamports)\n\n  // Players\n  player1: string;               // creator's wallet address\n  player1Side: CoinSide;         // \"heads\" | \"tails\"\n  player2: string | null;        // joiner's wallet address (null if not joined yet)\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null;  // opposite of player1 (null if no player2)\n\n  // Phase tracking\n  phase: CoinflipPhase;          // \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"\n  createdAt: number;            // timestamp (ms)\n  lockedAt?: number;            // when match entered LOCKED phase (ms) — when player2 joins\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;  // when countdown started (ms)\n  completedAt?: number;         // when match settled (ms)\n\n  // Result (null until settled)\n  result: CoinSide | null;       // \"heads\" | \"tails\" — only set when phase == \"complete\"\n  winner: string | null;         // winner's address (only if settled)\n\n  // Payout\n  claimed: boolean;              // has the winner claimed their payout?\n  payoutAmount: number;          // amount in SOL winner receives (50% of pool after 3% fee)\n\n  // VRF verification\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256 hash of server seed (shown pre-flip)\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed only after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for on-chain verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **Game Constants & Enums** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`)\n\nTier system:\n```typescript\ntype Tier = \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"diamond\";\n\nconst TIER_VALUES: Record<Tier, number> = {\n  iron: 0, bronze: 1, silver: 2, gold: 3, platinum: 4, diamond: 5\n};\n\nconst TIER_AMOUNTS: Record<Tier, number> = {\n  iron: 0.005,    // 0.005 SOL\n  bronze: 0.01,   // 0.01 SOL\n  silver: 0.1,    // 0.1 SOL\n  gold: 0.25,     // 0.25 SOL\n  platinum: 0.5,  // 0.5 SOL\n  diamond: 1.0    // 1.0 SOL\n};\n```\n\nCoin sides:\n```typescript\ntype CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\";\nconst COIN_SIDE_VALUES: Record<CoinSide, number> = {\n  heads: 0,\n  tails: 1\n};\n```\n\nFee split (3% total):\n```typescript\nconst FEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,              // 3% = 300 basis points\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200,   // 2.0% → platform revenue\n  RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS: 70,       // 0.7% → rakeback pool\n  CHEST_TREASURY_BPS: 30,      // 0.3% → treasure chests\n};\n```\n\n### 3. **On-Chain Account Structure** (`chain.ts` lines 76–95)\n\nThe on-chain match account has this layout:\n\n```typescript\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;                              // index 0–5\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };      // in lamports\n  creatorSide: number;                       // 0 = heads, 1 = tails\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;                  // { waiting: {} } | { locked: {} } | { settled: {} } etc.\n  result: number;                            // 0 = heads, 1 = tails (only when settled)\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };          // unix timestamp (seconds)\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;                  // Orao VRF randomness account key\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **On-Chain ↔ UI Conversion** (`chain.ts` lines 99–162)\n\nPhase mapping:\n```typescript\nOn-Chain               → UI\nwaiting                → \"created\"\nlocked                 → \"ready\"  (or \"complete\" if VRF fulfilled)\nsettled                → \"complete\"\nrefunded               → (filtered out in UI)\n```\n\nPayout calculation (from on-chain):\n```typescript\nconst entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\nconst totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;         // Both players' entries\nconst payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;        // After 3% fee\n// Winner gets payoutAmount, other player gets nothing\n```\n\n### 5. **Transaction Builders** (`chain.ts` lines 305–480)\n\n**Create Match** (`buildCreateMatchTx`):\n- Builder: `program.methods.createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)`\n- Accounts: creator, matchPda, configPda, systemProgram\n- Returns: Transaction + matchPda address\n\n**Join Match** (`buildJoinMatchTx`):\n- Builder: `program.methods.joinMatch()`\n- Accounts: opponent, matchPda, configPda, oraoProgram, oraoNetworkState, oraoTreasury, oraoRandom, systemProgram\n- VRF integration: Derives Orao network state and treasury from on-chain\n- VRF seed: match PDA bytes\n\n**Cancel Match** (`buildCancelMatchTx`):\n- Creator can cancel if match is still in \"waiting\" phase (no opponent)\n\n**Timeout Cancel** (`buildTimeoutCancelTx`):\n- Anyone can call if match is locked but VRF didn't resolve in time\n- Refunds both players and closes the match\n\n**Claim Payout** (`buildClaimPayoutTx`):\n- Either player can call (winner is derived on-chain from VRF randomness)\n- Reads VRF randomness from Orao account\n- Derives winner from `randomness[0] % 2`\n- Performs CPI to platform program to update player profiles (XP, stats)\n- Closes the match account and sends payout to winner\n\n### 6. **Game State Context** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\nManages:\n```typescript\n// State\nactiveMatch: UIMatch | null           // Currently opened match\nopenMatches: UIMatch[]                // All matches in \"waiting\" phase (lobby)\nclaimableMatches: UIMatch[]           // Matches player can settle/claim\nselectedTier: Tier | null\nselectedSide: CoinSide | null\n\n// Loading states\nloading, creating, joining, claiming  // In-flight flags\njoiningMatchId: string | null         // Which match is being joined\nerror: string | null\n\n// Verification\nlastClaimSignature: string | null     // Last claim tx for fairness verification\n\n// Actions\ncreateMatch(), joinMatch(matchId), cancelMatch(), timeoutCancel(), claimPayout()\nclearActiveMatch(), selectMatch(match), refreshMatches()\n```\n\n**Polling Strategy**:\n- In lobby (activeMatch == null): Poll every 30s → `refreshMatches()` (open + claimable)\n- In-game waiting for VRF (phase == \"ready\"): Poll every 5s → fetch active match\n- Animation intercept: ready → complete triggers 3s flip animation before showing result\n\n### 7. **Fairness Verification** (`verification.ts`)\n\nPost-claim, users can verify:\n```typescript\nverifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature): Promise<VerificationResult>\n\n// Extracts from MatchSettled event:\n{\n  verified: boolean,             // winner valid + VRF fulfilled\n  creator: string,\n  opponent: string,\n  winner: string,\n  randomnessHex: string,         // Full VRF randomness (hex)\n  derivedResult: \"heads\" | \"tails\",  // Re-derived from randomness[0] % 2\n  vrfFulfilled: boolean          // Confirmed in Orao account\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **PDA Derivation**\n\n```typescript\nMatch PDA:     PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()], COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID)\nConfig PDA:    PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")], COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID)\nOrao Network:  PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")], ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID)\nOrao Random:   PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), matchPda.toBytes()], ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID)\n```\n\n### 9. **Integration Points**\n\n- **VRF**: Orao Solana VRF (ephemeral randomness)\n- **Platform Program**: CPI for player profile updates (XP, stats) on claim\n- **Wallet**: `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (not Privy)\n- **On-chain IDL**: `CoinflipIDL` from `@rng-utopia/anchor-client`\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete domain model. All game logic flows through these types, converters, and transaction builders."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9a047ec0cb204f0c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48996\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 54851</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"339d09be-5189-43e7-b291-e94f665f152d","uuid":"459180d5-4e45-422b-8ee1-75c6e79546d6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the coinflip domain types and chain interaction layer. Please read:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state context\n4. Any constants file for coinflip (tiers, enums, etc.)\n\nReturn the full content of these files so I understand the domain model.","agentId":"a9a047ec0cb204f0c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the coinflip domain model:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Domain Model — Complete Overview\n\n### 1. **UIMatch Type** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts`)\n\nThe `UIMatch` interface represents a match as viewed in the frontend:\n\n```typescript\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string;                    // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier;                    // iron | bronze | silver | gold | platinum | diamond\n  entryAmount: number;           // in SOL (not lamports)\n\n  // Players\n  player1: string;               // creator's wallet address\n  player1Side: CoinSide;         // \"heads\" | \"tails\"\n  player2: string | null;        // joiner's wallet address (null if not joined yet)\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null;  // opposite of player1 (null if no player2)\n\n  // Phase tracking\n  phase: CoinflipPhase;          // \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"\n  createdAt: number;            // timestamp (ms)\n  lockedAt?: number;            // when match entered LOCKED phase (ms) — when player2 joins\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;  // when countdown started (ms)\n  completedAt?: number;         // when match settled (ms)\n\n  // Result (null until settled)\n  result: CoinSide | null;       // \"heads\" | \"tails\" — only set when phase == \"complete\"\n  winner: string | null;         // winner's address (only if settled)\n\n  // Payout\n  claimed: boolean;              // has the winner claimed their payout?\n  payoutAmount: number;          // amount in SOL winner receives (50% of pool after 3% fee)\n\n  // VRF verification\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256 hash of server seed (shown pre-flip)\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed only after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for on-chain verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **Game Constants & Enums** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`)\n\nTier system:\n```typescript\ntype Tier = \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"diamond\";\n\nconst TIER_VALUES: Record<Tier, number> = {\n  iron: 0, bronze: 1, silver: 2, gold: 3, platinum: 4, diamond: 5\n};\n\nconst TIER_AMOUNTS: Record<Tier, number> = {\n  iron: 0.005,    // 0.005 SOL\n  bronze: 0.01,   // 0.01 SOL\n  silver: 0.1,    // 0.1 SOL\n  gold: 0.25,     // 0.25 SOL\n  platinum: 0.5,  // 0.5 SOL\n  diamond: 1.0    // 1.0 SOL\n};\n```\n\nCoin sides:\n```typescript\ntype CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\";\nconst COIN_SIDE_VALUES: Record<CoinSide, number> = {\n  heads: 0,\n  tails: 1\n};\n```\n\nFee split (3% total):\n```typescript\nconst FEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,              // 3% = 300 basis points\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200,   // 2.0% → platform revenue\n  RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS: 70,       // 0.7% → rakeback pool\n  CHEST_TREASURY_BPS: 30,      // 0.3% → treasure chests\n};\n```\n\n### 3. **On-Chain Account Structure** (`chain.ts` lines 76–95)\n\nThe on-chain match account has this layout:\n\n```typescript\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;                              // index 0–5\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };      // in lamports\n  creatorSide: number;                       // 0 = heads, 1 = tails\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;                  // { waiting: {} } | { locked: {} } | { settled: {} } etc.\n  result: number;                            // 0 = heads, 1 = tails (only when settled)\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };          // unix timestamp (seconds)\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;                  // Orao VRF randomness account key\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **On-Chain ↔ UI Conversion** (`chain.ts` lines 99–162)\n\nPhase mapping:\n```typescript\nOn-Chain               → UI\nwaiting                → \"created\"\nlocked                 → \"ready\"  (or \"complete\" if VRF fulfilled)\nsettled                → \"complete\"\nrefunded               → (filtered out in UI)\n```\n\nPayout calculation (from on-chain):\n```typescript\nconst entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\nconst totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;         // Both players' entries\nconst payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;        // After 3% fee\n// Winner gets payoutAmount, other player gets nothing\n```\n\n### 5. **Transaction Builders** (`chain.ts` lines 305–480)\n\n**Create Match** (`buildCreateMatchTx`):\n- Builder: `program.methods.createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)`\n- Accounts: creator, matchPda, configPda, systemProgram\n- Returns: Transaction + matchPda address\n\n**Join Match** (`buildJoinMatchTx`):\n- Builder: `program.methods.joinMatch()`\n- Accounts: opponent, matchPda, configPda, oraoProgram, oraoNetworkState, oraoTreasury, oraoRandom, systemProgram\n- VRF integration: Derives Orao network state and treasury from on-chain\n- VRF seed: match PDA bytes\n\n**Cancel Match** (`buildCancelMatchTx`):\n- Creator can cancel if match is still in \"waiting\" phase (no opponent)\n\n**Timeout Cancel** (`buildTimeoutCancelTx`):\n- Anyone can call if match is locked but VRF didn't resolve in time\n- Refunds both players and closes the match\n\n**Claim Payout** (`buildClaimPayoutTx`):\n- Either player can call (winner is derived on-chain from VRF randomness)\n- Reads VRF randomness from Orao account\n- Derives winner from `randomness[0] % 2`\n- Performs CPI to platform program to update player profiles (XP, stats)\n- Closes the match account and sends payout to winner\n\n### 6. **Game State Context** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\nManages:\n```typescript\n// State\nactiveMatch: UIMatch | null           // Currently opened match\nopenMatches: UIMatch[]                // All matches in \"waiting\" phase (lobby)\nclaimableMatches: UIMatch[]           // Matches player can settle/claim\nselectedTier: Tier | null\nselectedSide: CoinSide | null\n\n// Loading states\nloading, creating, joining, claiming  // In-flight flags\njoiningMatchId: string | null         // Which match is being joined\nerror: string | null\n\n// Verification\nlastClaimSignature: string | null     // Last claim tx for fairness verification\n\n// Actions\ncreateMatch(), joinMatch(matchId), cancelMatch(), timeoutCancel(), claimPayout()\nclearActiveMatch(), selectMatch(match), refreshMatches()\n```\n\n**Polling Strategy**:\n- In lobby (activeMatch == null): Poll every 30s → `refreshMatches()` (open + claimable)\n- In-game waiting for VRF (phase == \"ready\"): Poll every 5s → fetch active match\n- Animation intercept: ready → complete triggers 3s flip animation before showing result\n\n### 7. **Fairness Verification** (`verification.ts`)\n\nPost-claim, users can verify:\n```typescript\nverifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature): Promise<VerificationResult>\n\n// Extracts from MatchSettled event:\n{\n  verified: boolean,             // winner valid + VRF fulfilled\n  creator: string,\n  opponent: string,\n  winner: string,\n  randomnessHex: string,         // Full VRF randomness (hex)\n  derivedResult: \"heads\" | \"tails\",  // Re-derived from randomness[0] % 2\n  vrfFulfilled: boolean          // Confirmed in Orao account\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **PDA Derivation**\n\n```typescript\nMatch PDA:     PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()], COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID)\nConfig PDA:    PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")], COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID)\nOrao Network:  PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")], ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID)\nOrao Random:   PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync([Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), matchPda.toBytes()], ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID)\n```\n\n### 9. **Integration Points**\n\n- **VRF**: Orao Solana VRF (ephemeral randomness)\n- **Platform Program**: CPI for player profile updates (XP, stats) on claim\n- **Wallet**: `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (not Privy)\n- **On-chain IDL**: `CoinflipIDL` from `@rng-utopia/anchor-client`\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete domain model. All game logic flows through these types, converters, and transaction builders."}],"totalDurationMs":54851,"totalTokens":48996,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2006,"cache_read_input_tokens":44415,"output_tokens":2571,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2006,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R7tqGeoym5azkT7Zf4QGRt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the coinflip UI structure. Let me create a detailed summary document with all the information needed for page-object helpers.\n\n## Coinflip UI Structure & Page Object Helpers Report\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the coinflip feature in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/`. Here's the complete breakdown for your page-object helper implementation:\n\n---\n\n### **Component Architecture**\n\n**Main Entry Point:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` - Full page with provider wrapper\n\n**Feature Components:**\n1. **OpenMatchesList** - Lobby/match list view\n2. **MatchCard** - Individual match card (for both lobby and claimable matches)\n3. **ActiveMatchView** - Active match detail view (all phases)\n4. **CoinSideSelector** - Heads/Tails picker\n5. **CoinAnimation** - Coin flip animation component\n6. **CoinflipContext** - State management with actions\n\n---\n\n### **Key UI Selectors & Class Names**\n\n#### **Main Page Structure**\n```\n.coinflip-main                          // Main game container\n.coinflip-lobby                         // Lobby view (when no active match)\n.coinflip-sidebar                       // Left sidebar\n.coinflip-error-toast                   // Error notification container\n```\n\n---\n\n### **CREATE MATCH FLOW**\n\n**Sidebar Components (when no active match):**\n```css\n/* Header */\n.coinflip-sidebar__title                // \"Create Game\"\n\n/* Tier Selection */\n.coinflip-sidebar__section              // Container for each section\n.coinflip-sidebar__label                // Label text (\"Select Tier\")\n.coinflip-sidebar__all-btn              // \"All\" button (filters matches by selected tier)\n\n/* Side Selection */\n.coinflip-side-selector                 // Container for Heads/Tails buttons\n  .coinflip-side-btn                    // Single button (Heads or Tails)\n  .coinflip-side-btn--heads             // Heads-specific styling\n  .coinflip-side-btn--tails             // Tails-specific styling\n  .coinflip-side-btn--selected          // Active selection state\n  .coinflip-side-btn__icon              // Icon container\n  .coinflip-side-btn__label             // Button label text\n\n/* Summary Display (shown when tier + side selected) */\n.coinflip-sidebar__summary              // Container for entry/payout preview\n.coinflip-sidebar__row                  // Entry | Payout rows\n.coinflip-sidebar__payout               // Payout amount text\n\n/* Create Button */\n.coinflip-action-btn                    // \"Create Game\" button (also used for other actions)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Create Match:**\n1. Click \"All\" button → filter matches by tier (optional)\n2. Select TierSelector (generic @rng-utopia/ui component)\n3. Click `.coinflip-side-btn--heads` or `.coinflip-side-btn--tails`\n4. Verify summary shows (\"Entry: $X\", \"Potential Payout: $Y\")\n5. Click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Create Game\")\n6. Button becomes disabled + text changes to \"Creating...\"\n\n---\n\n### **LOBBY / MATCH LIST FLOW**\n\n**Open Matches List Container:**\n```css\n.coinflip-matches                       // Container for all open matches\n.coinflip-matches__header               // Title + sort controls\n.coinflip-matches__title                // \"Open Games\" heading\n.coinflip-matches__controls             // Sort dropdown + count\n.coinflip-matches__sort                 // <select> with options: \"Newest\", \"Oldest\", \"Amount\"\n.coinflip-matches__count                // \"N available\" text\n.coinflip-matches__list                 // List of MatchCard components\n\n/* Loading State */\n.coinflip-matches--loading              // Container when loading\n.coinflip-matches__spinner              // Spinner animation\n  (text: \"Loading games...\")\n\n/* Empty State */\n.coinflip-matches--empty                // Container when no matches\n.coinflip-matches__empty-text           // No games message\n.coinflip-matches__empty-hint           // Hint text\n```\n\n**Match Card (for joining):**\n```css\n.coinflip-match-card                    // Container for each match\n  (no class if can join, add .coinflip-match-card--own if creator)\n\n.coinflip-match-card__creator           // Creator info section\n  .coinflip-match-card__address         // Creator's wallet address\n  .coinflip-match-card__time            // \"Xs ago\", \"Xm ago\", etc.\n\n.coinflip-match-card__bet               // Bet info section\n  .coinflip-match-card__side            // Coin side display (heads/tails)\n  .coinflip-match-card__amount          // Entry amount (colored by tier)\n\n.coinflip-match-card__actions           // Button container\n  .coinflip-match-card__join-btn        // \"Join\" button (disabled if own match or not connected)\n  .coinflip-match-card__status          // \"Waiting...\" (shown if own match)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Join Match:**\n1. Find desired match in `.coinflip-matches__list`\n2. Verify creator address in `.coinflip-match-card__address`\n3. Verify entry amount in `.coinflip-match-card__amount`\n4. Click `.coinflip-match-card__join-btn` (text = \"Join\")\n5. Button becomes disabled + text changes to \"Joining...\"\n6. Transitions to ActiveMatchView (phase = \"created\")\n\n---\n\n### **YOUR MATCHES (Claimable List)**\n\n**Container (shown when connected & have claimable matches):**\n```css\n.coinflip-your-matches                  // Claimable matches section (inherits from .coinflip-matches)\n.coinflip-matches__header               // \"Your Matches\" title + count\n.coinflip-match-card--claimable         // Claimable match variant (clickable div)\n  .coinflip-match-card__bet             // Entry amount\n  .coinflip-match-card__phase           // \"Waiting\" | \"Locked\" | \"Settled\" status badge\n  .coinflip-match-card__join-btn        // Action button (text varies):\n                                         // - \"Cancel\" (phase=\"created\" && is creator)\n                                         // - \"Claim\" (phase=\"complete\" && is winner)\n                                         // - \"Settle\" (phase=\"complete\" && is loser)\n                                         // - \"View\" (any other state)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Access Claimable Match:**\n1. Click on `.coinflip-match-card--claimable` div (role=\"button\", tabIndex=0)\n2. Transitions to ActiveMatchView with that match\n3. Same action buttons as ActiveMatchView apply\n\n---\n\n### **ACTIVE MATCH VIEW** (One Match Playing)\n\n**Container:**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match                  // Main container\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"created\" (Waiting for Opponent)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__waiting         // Container for waiting state\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Waiting for Opponent\"\n.coinflip-active-match__info            // Your side + Entry amount\n.coinflip-waiting__spinner              // Spinner animation\n.coinflip-active-match__hint            // \"Someone will join soon...\"\n.coinflip-action-btn--secondary         // \"Cancel Match\" button\n```\n\n**User Flow - Cancel Match:**\n1. Match in phase=\"created\" (waiting for opponent)\n2. Click `.coinflip-action-btn--secondary` (text = \"Cancel Match\")\n3. Button becomes disabled + text = \"Cancelling...\"\n4. Returns to lobby (clears activeMatch)\n\n#### **PHASE: \"ready\" (Both Players Joined)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__playing         // Container for ready/countdown/flipping states\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Game Ready!\"\n.coinflip-active-match__players         // Both players display\n  .coinflip-player--you                 // Your player section\n  .coinflip-player--opponent            // Opponent player section\n  .coinflip-player__label               // Avatar container\n  .coinflip-player__side                // \"HEADS\" | \"TAILS\" text (colored)\n.coinflip-active-match__vs              // \"VS\" separator\n\n.coinflip-coin-container                // Coin animation container\n  .coinflip-coin                        // Main coin element\n  .coinflip-coin--lg                    // Large coin (for active match)\n  .coinflip-coin__face--heads           // Heads face\n  .coinflip-coin__face--tails           // Tails face\n  .coinflip-coin__sprite                // Sprite image\n\n/* Timeout Cancel (appears after 2 min if VRF not resolved) */\n.coinflip-active-match__timeout         // Timeout info container\n.coinflip-active-match__hint            // \"Resolution timed out.\"\n.coinflip-action-btn--secondary         // \"Cancel & Refund\" button\n```\n\n**User Flow - Ready State Timeout:**\n1. Match locked at least 120 seconds (LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000)\n2. VRF not resolved yet\n3. \"Cancel & Refund\" button appears\n4. Click to cancel and refund both players\n\n#### **PHASE: \"countdown\" (3-2-1 Sequence)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // Shows countdown inline\n.coinflip-countdown-inline              // \"Flipping in...\" container\n.coinflip-countdown-inline__number      // Countdown number (3/2/1)\n                                         // Each number shows for exactly 1 second\n.coinflip-coin--lg                      // Static coin (not flipping yet)\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"flipping\" (Coin Spinning)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Flipping!\"\n.coinflip-coin--spinning-heads          // Spinning animation (if your side is heads)\n.coinflip-coin--spinning-tails          // Spinning animation (if your side is tails)\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"complete\" (Result Available)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // Colored title\n  .coinflip-active-match__title--won    // Green if winner\n  .coinflip-active-match__title--lost   // Red if loser\n  .coinflip-lose-title                  // \"You Lost 💔\" + shard animation\n\n.coinflip-win-animation                 // Star burst + coin animation (if winner)\n.coinflip-result                        // Result display container\n  .coinflip-result--won                 // Green styling if winner\n  .coinflip-result--lost                // Red styling if loser\n  .coinflip-result__outcome             // \"Result: HEADS\" | \"Result: TAILS\"\n  .coinflip-result__payout              // \"Payout: $X\" (winner only)\n\n.coinflip-active-match__actions         // Action button container\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Claim Payout\" (winner) or \"Settle & Return to Lobby\" (loser)\n                                         // Disabled until on-chain settlement complete\n\n/* Post-Claim Actions */\n.coinflip-active-match__post-claim      // Shown after claiming\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Verify Fairness\" button (if claimTxSignature exists)\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Play Again\" button (rematch)\n  .coinflip-action-btn--secondary       // \"Back to Lobby\" button\n\n.coinflip-verification                  // Fairness verification panel\n  .coinflip-verification__title         // \"Fairness Verification\"\n  .coinflip-verification__badge         // \"Verified\" or \"Failed\" badge\n    .coinflip-verification__badge--verified\n    .coinflip-verification__badge--failed\n  .coinflip-verification__rows          // Details\n    .coinflip-verification__row         // Each row (Claim TX, Randomness, etc.)\n    .coinflip-verification__hash        // Hash display\n    .coinflip-verification__check       // \"Yes\" checkmark\n    .coinflip-verification__cross       // \"No\" cross\n  .coinflip-verification__link          // \"Full Verification Page →\" link\n```\n\n**User Flow - Claim Payout:**\n1. Match complete (phase=\"complete\")\n2. Click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Claim Payout\" or \"Settle & Return to Lobby\")\n3. Button disabled + text = \"Settling...\"\n4. On-chain settlement executes\n5. `match.claimed = true` → shows post-claim actions\n\n**User Flow - Rematch:**\n1. After claiming, click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Play Again\")\n2. Sets tier/side from previous match\n3. Clears active match and triggers create\n4. Returns to lobby with tier/side pre-selected\n\n**User Flow - Verify Fairness:**\n1. After claiming, click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Verify Fairness\")\n2. Button disabled + text = \"Verifying...\"\n3. On verification complete, shows `.coinflip-verification` panel\n4. Button becomes \"Verified\" (disabled)\n\n**User Flow - Back to Lobby:**\n1. After claiming or at any complete state, click `.coinflip-action-btn--secondary` (text = \"Back to Lobby\")\n2. Dismisses match, returns to lobby\n3. Re-enables lobby match polling\n\n---\n\n### **SIDEBAR - ACTIVE MATCH STATE**\n\n**Current Game Info:**\n```css\n.coinflip-sidebar__title                // \"Current Game\"\n.coinflip-sidebar__game-info            // Match info container\n\n.coinflip-sidebar__row                  // Each row (Tier, Side, Entry, Pot, Status)\n  .coinflip-sidebar__tier               // Tier text (colored by tier color)\n  .coinflip-sidebar__pot                // Total pot amount\n  .coinflip-sidebar__status             // Phase text (\"Waiting...\" | \"Ready!\" | \"Countdown...\" | \"Flipping...\" | \"Complete\")\n\n.coinflip-sidebar__fairness             // Fairness section\n.coinflip-sidebar__fairness-title       // \"Round Fairness\" with lock emoji\n  .coinflip-sidebar__fairness-row       // Match ID, Seed Hash, Server Seed (post-complete), Block Hash\n  .coinflip-sidebar__hash               // Hash display\n  .coinflip-sidebar__hash--revealed     // Server Seed (revealed only after settle)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **ERROR HANDLING**\n\n```css\n.coinflip-error-toast                   // Error notification container\n  .rng-toast                            // Toast component (from @rng-utopia/ui)\n  .rng-toast__message                   // Error message text\n```\n\n**Error Messages (from CoinflipContext):**\n- \"Wallet not connected...\" → Connect action needed\n- \"Select tier and side first.\" → Validation\n- \"You already have an active match.\" → Pre-check before create\n- \"Transaction cancelled by user.\" → User rejected\n- \"Insufficient balance...\" → Not enough SOL\n- \"This match no longer available.\" → Race condition\n- \"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\" → Join race\n- And others (see parseTransactionError in context)\n\n---\n\n### **BUTTON TEXT BY STATE**\n\n| Action | Initial Text | Loading Text | Success/Disabled Text |\n|--------|--------------|--------------|----------------------|\n| Connect Wallet | \"Connect Wallet\" | (no loading) | N/A |\n| Create Game | \"Create Game\" | \"Creating...\" | (disabled) |\n| Join Match | \"Join\" | \"Joining...\" | (disabled) |\n| Cancel Match | \"Cancel Match\" | \"Cancelling...\" | N/A |\n| Claim/Settle | \"Claim Payout\" / \"Settle & Return\" | \"Settling...\" | N/A |\n| Verify Fairness | \"Verify Fairness\" | \"Verifying...\" | \"Verified\" |\n| Play Again | \"Play Again\" | \"Creating...\" | (disabled) |\n| Back to Lobby | \"Back to Lobby\" | (no loading) | N/A |\n| Cancel & Refund | \"Cancel & Refund\" | \"Cancelling...\" | N/A |\n| All Filter | \"All\" | N/A | Active state added |\n\n---\n\n### **DATA ATTRIBUTES & ROLES**\n\n**No existing data-testid attributes found** in the codebase. You'll need to add them during your test implementation.\n\n**Suggested data-testid structure:**\n```\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-sidebar\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-tier-selector\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-side-selector\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-create-btn\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-lobby\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-open-matches\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-match-card-[matchId]\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-join-btn-[matchId]\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-active-match\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-claim-btn\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-verify-btn\"\n```\n\n**Existing Roles/Semantics:**\n- Claimable match card: `role=\"button\"` `tabIndex={0}`\n- Standard buttons: `type=\"button\"`\n- Sort dropdown: `<select>` element\n- Modals: Modal component from @rng-utopia/ui\n\n---\n\n### **CONTEXT API (State Management)**\n\n**Hook:** `useCoinflip()`\n\n**State:**\n- `activeMatch: UIMatch | null`\n- `openMatches: UIMatch[]`\n- `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]`\n- `selectedTier: Tier | null`\n- `selectedSide: CoinSide | null`\n- `loading: boolean` (lobby loading)\n- `creating: boolean` (create in progress)\n- `joining: boolean` (join in progress)\n- `claiming: boolean` (claim in progress)\n- `joiningMatchId: string | null` (which match is joining)\n- `error: string | null`\n- `lastClaimSignature: string | null` (for verification)\n\n**Actions:**\n- `setSelectedTier(tier)`\n- `setSelectedSide(side)`\n- `createMatch()` → requires publicKey, selectedTier, selectedSide\n- `joinMatch(matchId)` → requires publicKey\n- `cancelMatch()` → requires activeMatch\n- `timeoutCancel()` → requires activeMatch with player2\n- `claimPayout()` → requires activeMatch with player2\n- `clearActiveMatch()` → returns to lobby\n- `selectMatch(match)` → open claimable match\n- `refreshMatches()` → poll open/claimable matches\n- `clearError()`\n\n---\n\n### **MATCH PHASES (UIMatch.phase)**\n\n1. **\"created\"** - P1 waiting for P2 to join\n2. **\"ready\"** - Both players present, awaiting VRF result\n3. **\"countdown\"** - 3-2-1 countdown (1 sec each)\n4. **\"flipping\"** - Coin spinning (3 sec animation)\n5. **\"complete\"** - Result available, awaiting claim\n\n---\n\n### **UIMatch Type (Key Fields)**\n\n```typescript\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string;                    // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier;                    // \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"emerald\"\n  entryAmount: number;           // $ amount\n  \n  // Players\n  player1: string;               // Creator wallet address\n  player1Side: CoinSide;         // \"heads\" | \"tails\"\n  player2: string | null;        // Joiner wallet address\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null;  // \"heads\" | \"tails\" (opposite of P1)\n  \n  // Timing\n  phase: CoinflipPhase;\n  createdAt: number;             // Timestamp (ms)\n  lockedAt?: number;             // When entered \"ready\" phase\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;   // When countdown began\n  completedAt?: number;          // When result available\n  \n  // Result\n  result: CoinSide | null;       // Final coin result\n  winner: string | null;         // Winner's wallet address\n  claimed: boolean;              // Whether settlement claimed on-chain\n  payoutAmount: number;          // $ winner receives (after fees)\n  \n  // Fairness\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256(serverSeed) shown before flip\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Key Constants**\n\nFrom the codebase:\n\n```typescript\n// From CoinflipPage.tsx\nconst SIDE_COLORS = {\n  heads: \"#45b058\",    // Green\n  tails: \"#e09030\",    // Orange\n};\n\n// Lock timeout for timeout-cancel action\nconst LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000; // 2 minutes\n\n// Flip animation delay (ready → flipping → complete)\nconst FLIP_ANIMATION_DURATION = 3000; // 3 seconds\n\n// Poll intervals\nconst FAST_POLL_INTERVAL = 5000;   // 5s while awaiting VRF (ready phase)\nconst SLOW_POLL_INTERVAL = 30000;  // 30s for lobby polling\n```\n\n---\n\n### **CSS Variables & Responsive Breakpoints**\n\nSide colors are applied via inline styles:\n```typescript\ncolor: match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\"\ntextShadow: `0 0 6px ${match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\"}`\n```\n\n---\n\nThis gives you everything needed to write comprehensive page-object helpers covering all user flows, button states, error scenarios, and match lifecycle phases. The class names and component structure are fully documented above."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1ad8aca6647529bc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65941\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 103992</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"339d09be-5189-43e7-b291-e94f665f152d","uuid":"5a75adb6-f82d-4503-bc34-13e01c33a792","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the coinflip UI structure to write page-object helpers. Please find and read:\n1. The main coinflip page/route component\n2. Components for creating a match (tier selector, coin picker, create button)\n3. Components for the lobby/match list\n4. Components for joining, claiming, canceling a match\n5. Any existing data-testid attributes\n\nLook in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/` and related routing files.\n\nReturn the key selectors (data-testid, button text, role attributes) and the user flow for each action (create, join, claim, cancel). Be thorough - read the actual component files.","agentId":"a1ad8aca6647529bc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the coinflip UI structure. Let me create a detailed summary document with all the information needed for page-object helpers.\n\n## Coinflip UI Structure & Page Object Helpers Report\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the coinflip feature in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/`. Here's the complete breakdown for your page-object helper implementation:\n\n---\n\n### **Component Architecture**\n\n**Main Entry Point:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` - Full page with provider wrapper\n\n**Feature Components:**\n1. **OpenMatchesList** - Lobby/match list view\n2. **MatchCard** - Individual match card (for both lobby and claimable matches)\n3. **ActiveMatchView** - Active match detail view (all phases)\n4. **CoinSideSelector** - Heads/Tails picker\n5. **CoinAnimation** - Coin flip animation component\n6. **CoinflipContext** - State management with actions\n\n---\n\n### **Key UI Selectors & Class Names**\n\n#### **Main Page Structure**\n```\n.coinflip-main                          // Main game container\n.coinflip-lobby                         // Lobby view (when no active match)\n.coinflip-sidebar                       // Left sidebar\n.coinflip-error-toast                   // Error notification container\n```\n\n---\n\n### **CREATE MATCH FLOW**\n\n**Sidebar Components (when no active match):**\n```css\n/* Header */\n.coinflip-sidebar__title                // \"Create Game\"\n\n/* Tier Selection */\n.coinflip-sidebar__section              // Container for each section\n.coinflip-sidebar__label                // Label text (\"Select Tier\")\n.coinflip-sidebar__all-btn              // \"All\" button (filters matches by selected tier)\n\n/* Side Selection */\n.coinflip-side-selector                 // Container for Heads/Tails buttons\n  .coinflip-side-btn                    // Single button (Heads or Tails)\n  .coinflip-side-btn--heads             // Heads-specific styling\n  .coinflip-side-btn--tails             // Tails-specific styling\n  .coinflip-side-btn--selected          // Active selection state\n  .coinflip-side-btn__icon              // Icon container\n  .coinflip-side-btn__label             // Button label text\n\n/* Summary Display (shown when tier + side selected) */\n.coinflip-sidebar__summary              // Container for entry/payout preview\n.coinflip-sidebar__row                  // Entry | Payout rows\n.coinflip-sidebar__payout               // Payout amount text\n\n/* Create Button */\n.coinflip-action-btn                    // \"Create Game\" button (also used for other actions)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Create Match:**\n1. Click \"All\" button → filter matches by tier (optional)\n2. Select TierSelector (generic @rng-utopia/ui component)\n3. Click `.coinflip-side-btn--heads` or `.coinflip-side-btn--tails`\n4. Verify summary shows (\"Entry: $X\", \"Potential Payout: $Y\")\n5. Click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Create Game\")\n6. Button becomes disabled + text changes to \"Creating...\"\n\n---\n\n### **LOBBY / MATCH LIST FLOW**\n\n**Open Matches List Container:**\n```css\n.coinflip-matches                       // Container for all open matches\n.coinflip-matches__header               // Title + sort controls\n.coinflip-matches__title                // \"Open Games\" heading\n.coinflip-matches__controls             // Sort dropdown + count\n.coinflip-matches__sort                 // <select> with options: \"Newest\", \"Oldest\", \"Amount\"\n.coinflip-matches__count                // \"N available\" text\n.coinflip-matches__list                 // List of MatchCard components\n\n/* Loading State */\n.coinflip-matches--loading              // Container when loading\n.coinflip-matches__spinner              // Spinner animation\n  (text: \"Loading games...\")\n\n/* Empty State */\n.coinflip-matches--empty                // Container when no matches\n.coinflip-matches__empty-text           // No games message\n.coinflip-matches__empty-hint           // Hint text\n```\n\n**Match Card (for joining):**\n```css\n.coinflip-match-card                    // Container for each match\n  (no class if can join, add .coinflip-match-card--own if creator)\n\n.coinflip-match-card__creator           // Creator info section\n  .coinflip-match-card__address         // Creator's wallet address\n  .coinflip-match-card__time            // \"Xs ago\", \"Xm ago\", etc.\n\n.coinflip-match-card__bet               // Bet info section\n  .coinflip-match-card__side            // Coin side display (heads/tails)\n  .coinflip-match-card__amount          // Entry amount (colored by tier)\n\n.coinflip-match-card__actions           // Button container\n  .coinflip-match-card__join-btn        // \"Join\" button (disabled if own match or not connected)\n  .coinflip-match-card__status          // \"Waiting...\" (shown if own match)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Join Match:**\n1. Find desired match in `.coinflip-matches__list`\n2. Verify creator address in `.coinflip-match-card__address`\n3. Verify entry amount in `.coinflip-match-card__amount`\n4. Click `.coinflip-match-card__join-btn` (text = \"Join\")\n5. Button becomes disabled + text changes to \"Joining...\"\n6. Transitions to ActiveMatchView (phase = \"created\")\n\n---\n\n### **YOUR MATCHES (Claimable List)**\n\n**Container (shown when connected & have claimable matches):**\n```css\n.coinflip-your-matches                  // Claimable matches section (inherits from .coinflip-matches)\n.coinflip-matches__header               // \"Your Matches\" title + count\n.coinflip-match-card--claimable         // Claimable match variant (clickable div)\n  .coinflip-match-card__bet             // Entry amount\n  .coinflip-match-card__phase           // \"Waiting\" | \"Locked\" | \"Settled\" status badge\n  .coinflip-match-card__join-btn        // Action button (text varies):\n                                         // - \"Cancel\" (phase=\"created\" && is creator)\n                                         // - \"Claim\" (phase=\"complete\" && is winner)\n                                         // - \"Settle\" (phase=\"complete\" && is loser)\n                                         // - \"View\" (any other state)\n```\n\n**User Flow - Access Claimable Match:**\n1. Click on `.coinflip-match-card--claimable` div (role=\"button\", tabIndex=0)\n2. Transitions to ActiveMatchView with that match\n3. Same action buttons as ActiveMatchView apply\n\n---\n\n### **ACTIVE MATCH VIEW** (One Match Playing)\n\n**Container:**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match                  // Main container\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"created\" (Waiting for Opponent)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__waiting         // Container for waiting state\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Waiting for Opponent\"\n.coinflip-active-match__info            // Your side + Entry amount\n.coinflip-waiting__spinner              // Spinner animation\n.coinflip-active-match__hint            // \"Someone will join soon...\"\n.coinflip-action-btn--secondary         // \"Cancel Match\" button\n```\n\n**User Flow - Cancel Match:**\n1. Match in phase=\"created\" (waiting for opponent)\n2. Click `.coinflip-action-btn--secondary` (text = \"Cancel Match\")\n3. Button becomes disabled + text = \"Cancelling...\"\n4. Returns to lobby (clears activeMatch)\n\n#### **PHASE: \"ready\" (Both Players Joined)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__playing         // Container for ready/countdown/flipping states\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Game Ready!\"\n.coinflip-active-match__players         // Both players display\n  .coinflip-player--you                 // Your player section\n  .coinflip-player--opponent            // Opponent player section\n  .coinflip-player__label               // Avatar container\n  .coinflip-player__side                // \"HEADS\" | \"TAILS\" text (colored)\n.coinflip-active-match__vs              // \"VS\" separator\n\n.coinflip-coin-container                // Coin animation container\n  .coinflip-coin                        // Main coin element\n  .coinflip-coin--lg                    // Large coin (for active match)\n  .coinflip-coin__face--heads           // Heads face\n  .coinflip-coin__face--tails           // Tails face\n  .coinflip-coin__sprite                // Sprite image\n\n/* Timeout Cancel (appears after 2 min if VRF not resolved) */\n.coinflip-active-match__timeout         // Timeout info container\n.coinflip-active-match__hint            // \"Resolution timed out.\"\n.coinflip-action-btn--secondary         // \"Cancel & Refund\" button\n```\n\n**User Flow - Ready State Timeout:**\n1. Match locked at least 120 seconds (LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000)\n2. VRF not resolved yet\n3. \"Cancel & Refund\" button appears\n4. Click to cancel and refund both players\n\n#### **PHASE: \"countdown\" (3-2-1 Sequence)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // Shows countdown inline\n.coinflip-countdown-inline              // \"Flipping in...\" container\n.coinflip-countdown-inline__number      // Countdown number (3/2/1)\n                                         // Each number shows for exactly 1 second\n.coinflip-coin--lg                      // Static coin (not flipping yet)\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"flipping\" (Coin Spinning)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // \"Flipping!\"\n.coinflip-coin--spinning-heads          // Spinning animation (if your side is heads)\n.coinflip-coin--spinning-tails          // Spinning animation (if your side is tails)\n```\n\n#### **PHASE: \"complete\" (Result Available)**\n```css\n.coinflip-active-match__title           // Colored title\n  .coinflip-active-match__title--won    // Green if winner\n  .coinflip-active-match__title--lost   // Red if loser\n  .coinflip-lose-title                  // \"You Lost 💔\" + shard animation\n\n.coinflip-win-animation                 // Star burst + coin animation (if winner)\n.coinflip-result                        // Result display container\n  .coinflip-result--won                 // Green styling if winner\n  .coinflip-result--lost                // Red styling if loser\n  .coinflip-result__outcome             // \"Result: HEADS\" | \"Result: TAILS\"\n  .coinflip-result__payout              // \"Payout: $X\" (winner only)\n\n.coinflip-active-match__actions         // Action button container\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Claim Payout\" (winner) or \"Settle & Return to Lobby\" (loser)\n                                         // Disabled until on-chain settlement complete\n\n/* Post-Claim Actions */\n.coinflip-active-match__post-claim      // Shown after claiming\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Verify Fairness\" button (if claimTxSignature exists)\n  .coinflip-action-btn                  // \"Play Again\" button (rematch)\n  .coinflip-action-btn--secondary       // \"Back to Lobby\" button\n\n.coinflip-verification                  // Fairness verification panel\n  .coinflip-verification__title         // \"Fairness Verification\"\n  .coinflip-verification__badge         // \"Verified\" or \"Failed\" badge\n    .coinflip-verification__badge--verified\n    .coinflip-verification__badge--failed\n  .coinflip-verification__rows          // Details\n    .coinflip-verification__row         // Each row (Claim TX, Randomness, etc.)\n    .coinflip-verification__hash        // Hash display\n    .coinflip-verification__check       // \"Yes\" checkmark\n    .coinflip-verification__cross       // \"No\" cross\n  .coinflip-verification__link          // \"Full Verification Page →\" link\n```\n\n**User Flow - Claim Payout:**\n1. Match complete (phase=\"complete\")\n2. Click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Claim Payout\" or \"Settle & Return to Lobby\")\n3. Button disabled + text = \"Settling...\"\n4. On-chain settlement executes\n5. `match.claimed = true` → shows post-claim actions\n\n**User Flow - Rematch:**\n1. After claiming, click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Play Again\")\n2. Sets tier/side from previous match\n3. Clears active match and triggers create\n4. Returns to lobby with tier/side pre-selected\n\n**User Flow - Verify Fairness:**\n1. After claiming, click `.coinflip-action-btn` (text = \"Verify Fairness\")\n2. Button disabled + text = \"Verifying...\"\n3. On verification complete, shows `.coinflip-verification` panel\n4. Button becomes \"Verified\" (disabled)\n\n**User Flow - Back to Lobby:**\n1. After claiming or at any complete state, click `.coinflip-action-btn--secondary` (text = \"Back to Lobby\")\n2. Dismisses match, returns to lobby\n3. Re-enables lobby match polling\n\n---\n\n### **SIDEBAR - ACTIVE MATCH STATE**\n\n**Current Game Info:**\n```css\n.coinflip-sidebar__title                // \"Current Game\"\n.coinflip-sidebar__game-info            // Match info container\n\n.coinflip-sidebar__row                  // Each row (Tier, Side, Entry, Pot, Status)\n  .coinflip-sidebar__tier               // Tier text (colored by tier color)\n  .coinflip-sidebar__pot                // Total pot amount\n  .coinflip-sidebar__status             // Phase text (\"Waiting...\" | \"Ready!\" | \"Countdown...\" | \"Flipping...\" | \"Complete\")\n\n.coinflip-sidebar__fairness             // Fairness section\n.coinflip-sidebar__fairness-title       // \"Round Fairness\" with lock emoji\n  .coinflip-sidebar__fairness-row       // Match ID, Seed Hash, Server Seed (post-complete), Block Hash\n  .coinflip-sidebar__hash               // Hash display\n  .coinflip-sidebar__hash--revealed     // Server Seed (revealed only after settle)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **ERROR HANDLING**\n\n```css\n.coinflip-error-toast                   // Error notification container\n  .rng-toast                            // Toast component (from @rng-utopia/ui)\n  .rng-toast__message                   // Error message text\n```\n\n**Error Messages (from CoinflipContext):**\n- \"Wallet not connected...\" → Connect action needed\n- \"Select tier and side first.\" → Validation\n- \"You already have an active match.\" → Pre-check before create\n- \"Transaction cancelled by user.\" → User rejected\n- \"Insufficient balance...\" → Not enough SOL\n- \"This match no longer available.\" → Race condition\n- \"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\" → Join race\n- And others (see parseTransactionError in context)\n\n---\n\n### **BUTTON TEXT BY STATE**\n\n| Action | Initial Text | Loading Text | Success/Disabled Text |\n|--------|--------------|--------------|----------------------|\n| Connect Wallet | \"Connect Wallet\" | (no loading) | N/A |\n| Create Game | \"Create Game\" | \"Creating...\" | (disabled) |\n| Join Match | \"Join\" | \"Joining...\" | (disabled) |\n| Cancel Match | \"Cancel Match\" | \"Cancelling...\" | N/A |\n| Claim/Settle | \"Claim Payout\" / \"Settle & Return\" | \"Settling...\" | N/A |\n| Verify Fairness | \"Verify Fairness\" | \"Verifying...\" | \"Verified\" |\n| Play Again | \"Play Again\" | \"Creating...\" | (disabled) |\n| Back to Lobby | \"Back to Lobby\" | (no loading) | N/A |\n| Cancel & Refund | \"Cancel & Refund\" | \"Cancelling...\" | N/A |\n| All Filter | \"All\" | N/A | Active state added |\n\n---\n\n### **DATA ATTRIBUTES & ROLES**\n\n**No existing data-testid attributes found** in the codebase. You'll need to add them during your test implementation.\n\n**Suggested data-testid structure:**\n```\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-sidebar\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-tier-selector\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-side-selector\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-create-btn\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-lobby\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-open-matches\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-match-card-[matchId]\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-join-btn-[matchId]\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-active-match\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-claim-btn\"\ndata-testid=\"coinflip-verify-btn\"\n```\n\n**Existing Roles/Semantics:**\n- Claimable match card: `role=\"button\"` `tabIndex={0}`\n- Standard buttons: `type=\"button\"`\n- Sort dropdown: `<select>` element\n- Modals: Modal component from @rng-utopia/ui\n\n---\n\n### **CONTEXT API (State Management)**\n\n**Hook:** `useCoinflip()`\n\n**State:**\n- `activeMatch: UIMatch | null`\n- `openMatches: UIMatch[]`\n- `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]`\n- `selectedTier: Tier | null`\n- `selectedSide: CoinSide | null`\n- `loading: boolean` (lobby loading)\n- `creating: boolean` (create in progress)\n- `joining: boolean` (join in progress)\n- `claiming: boolean` (claim in progress)\n- `joiningMatchId: string | null` (which match is joining)\n- `error: string | null`\n- `lastClaimSignature: string | null` (for verification)\n\n**Actions:**\n- `setSelectedTier(tier)`\n- `setSelectedSide(side)`\n- `createMatch()` → requires publicKey, selectedTier, selectedSide\n- `joinMatch(matchId)` → requires publicKey\n- `cancelMatch()` → requires activeMatch\n- `timeoutCancel()` → requires activeMatch with player2\n- `claimPayout()` → requires activeMatch with player2\n- `clearActiveMatch()` → returns to lobby\n- `selectMatch(match)` → open claimable match\n- `refreshMatches()` → poll open/claimable matches\n- `clearError()`\n\n---\n\n### **MATCH PHASES (UIMatch.phase)**\n\n1. **\"created\"** - P1 waiting for P2 to join\n2. **\"ready\"** - Both players present, awaiting VRF result\n3. **\"countdown\"** - 3-2-1 countdown (1 sec each)\n4. **\"flipping\"** - Coin spinning (3 sec animation)\n5. **\"complete\"** - Result available, awaiting claim\n\n---\n\n### **UIMatch Type (Key Fields)**\n\n```typescript\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string;                    // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier;                    // \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"emerald\"\n  entryAmount: number;           // $ amount\n  \n  // Players\n  player1: string;               // Creator wallet address\n  player1Side: CoinSide;         // \"heads\" | \"tails\"\n  player2: string | null;        // Joiner wallet address\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null;  // \"heads\" | \"tails\" (opposite of P1)\n  \n  // Timing\n  phase: CoinflipPhase;\n  createdAt: number;             // Timestamp (ms)\n  lockedAt?: number;             // When entered \"ready\" phase\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;   // When countdown began\n  completedAt?: number;          // When result available\n  \n  // Result\n  result: CoinSide | null;       // Final coin result\n  winner: string | null;         // Winner's wallet address\n  claimed: boolean;              // Whether settlement claimed on-chain\n  payoutAmount: number;          // $ winner receives (after fees)\n  \n  // Fairness\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256(serverSeed) shown before flip\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Key Constants**\n\nFrom the codebase:\n\n```typescript\n// From CoinflipPage.tsx\nconst SIDE_COLORS = {\n  heads: \"#45b058\",    // Green\n  tails: \"#e09030\",    // Orange\n};\n\n// Lock timeout for timeout-cancel action\nconst LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000; // 2 minutes\n\n// Flip animation delay (ready → flipping → complete)\nconst FLIP_ANIMATION_DURATION = 3000; // 3 seconds\n\n// Poll intervals\nconst FAST_POLL_INTERVAL = 5000;   // 5s while awaiting VRF (ready phase)\nconst SLOW_POLL_INTERVAL = 30000;  // 30s for lobby polling\n```\n\n---\n\n### **CSS Variables & Responsive Breakpoints**\n\nSide colors are applied via inline styles:\n```typescript\ncolor: match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\"\ntextShadow: `0 0 6px ${match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\"}`\n```\n\n---\n\nThis gives you everything needed to write comprehensive page-object helpers covering all user flows, button states, error scenarios, and match lifecycle phases. The class names and component structure are fully documented above."}],"totalDurationMs":103992,"totalTokens":65941,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1067,"cache_read_input_tokens":59304,"output_tokens":5570,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1067,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0174TZWxNsaF8fLikvHXnJ4r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create the shared E2E helpers file. The checklist item is:\n\n> `[test] Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives`\n\nI need to create page-object methods that use CSS class selectors (since there are no data-testid attributes). Let me create helpers that:\n\n1. **Selectors** - CSS class-based selectors for all key UI elements\n2. **Page-object methods** for:\n   - `createMatch(page, tier, side)` - select tier, select side, click create\n   - `joinMatch(page, matchId?)` - find and join a match in the lobby\n   - `claimPayout(page)` - claim the payout after a match completes\n   - `cancelMatch(page)` - cancel an active match\n3. **Wait/assert primitives** like `waitForPhase()` to track match state changes, `waitForLobbyMatch()` to detect new matches appearing, `assertMatchResult()` to verify outcomes, and `assertNoConsoleErrors()` to catch any runtime issues\n\n.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the CSS selectors I'll need for the test interactions. For the create flow, I need to target the tier selector component from the UI library, the heads/tails buttons, and the create button. For the lobby and join flows, I'm looking at the match list container, individual match cards, and the join button within each card.\n\nFor the claim and cancel flows, I need selectors for the active match display, win/loss titles, and action buttons for claiming payouts or settling matches. I'm considering whether to use text-based selectors with Playwright since they tend to be more resilient than class-based selectors, especially for components from external UI packages like the TierSelector.\n\nNow I need to check how the TierSelector actually renders in the UI so I can properly select tiers in my test helpers.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4826,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6620,"cache_read_input_tokens":42928,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6620},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"339d09be-5189-43e7-b291-e94f665f152d","uuid":"acaee1f1-b8be-45fe-8416-c486c24e55b3"}
